<br>
I've been sneaking into Neriak since I was level 11. I wasn't found out once until my mid teens. About that time (level 15 or so) I killed my first inkie inside the city itself. Her name was Seleina and here's what happened...<br>
<br>
There was a necromancer out in Nektulos that spotted me earlier that evening. He tried to do the regular PvP thing, and it was a close fight, but he eventually ran to the guards at the bridge. His name was Aargorroth. After he ran he messaged me with &quot;good fight&quot; yada yada yada. (note: I have since then become more courageous and follow my opponents to the bridge after they run... but more about that later) We both wanted a rematch.<br>
<br>
So we decided to meet in a secluded spot and /duel. I let him summon a pet (/con'd easy blue to me), buff himself, and then meditate to full. The duel was rough.. but a rogue with fast weapons can beat a caster every time. Normally when fighting a character with a pet I go for the pet first... but this time I decided to off the owner of the pet. I won the duel with little over a bubble of health left. Little did I know the inkie woman Seleina was watching the duel from afar. She came right in after I won and killed me.<br>
<br>
One thing that surprises my opponents most is my excellent memory (yellow stickies next to my monitor). I never forget my opponents who get away or those that actually defeat me.<br>
<br>
After I retrieved my corpse I noticed that Seleina was still online. She wasn't in Nektulos and I had a friend check if she was in East Commonlands or Freeport area. Nope.. hmm, so she must be in Neriak.<br>
<br>
To make this really long story short... I snuck into Neriak (using the techniques I'm going to describe in a new thread) and found her right outside the Toadstool in Neriak Commons. She was at about 1/4 health, and bandaging. She probably gated in to avoid death out in the wilderness. Muhaha.<br>
<br>
It was really risky attacking her outside Toadstool. There are a few roaming guards out there but I didn't see any in sight. I backstabbed, pierced a few times and she went down fast. She had time to blurt out &quot;oh my god&quot; right before her last breath of air. I think I taught her a lesson about messing with rogues. <br>
<br>
